# Windows 8 API sets

API Sets available in Windows 8 and Windows Server 2012.

## API Sets available in Windows 8 and Windows Server 2012

This topic lists the API Sets available for use in Windows 8 and Windows Server 2012. For convenience, the "umbrella" libs MinCore.lib and MinCore\_Downlevel.lib are provided in the Microsoft Windows Software Development Kit (SDK) that encompasses the API surface defined in API Sets plus additional APIs that are contained in well-layered system DLLs.

> [!Note]  
> **Compatibility with Windows 7, Windows Server 2008 R2 and older operating systems:** Binaries that link to MinCore.lib or MinCore\_Downlevel.lib are not designed to work on Windows 7, Windows Server 2008 R2 or earlier. Binaries that need to run on earlier versions of Windows or Windows Server must not use either MinCore.lib or MinCore\_Downlevel.lib.

 

## Lib to link to: MinCore.lib

The API Sets listed in this table are the DLL names to use for delay load.
